Evaluation metric: We use the Dice Similarity Coefficient (DSC) to evaluate segmentation performance. DSC is a common choice in unsupervised domain adaptation medical segmentation tasks [15], [21], [43], which can be defined as:
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym}
\usepackage{amsfonts}
\usepackage{amssymb}
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}
\begin{equation*}
{\it DSC}(\mathrm{A}, \mathrm{B})=\frac{2 \times |\mathrm{A} \cap \mathrm{B}|}{|\mathrm{A}|+|\mathrm{B}|} \tag{7}
\end{equation*}
\end{document}where A and B represent the lung region of prediction and ground truth, respectively.

For classification evaluation, accuracy, F1-score, recall and precision are employed, which can be written as:
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym}
\usepackage{amsfonts}
\usepackage{amssymb}
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}
\begin{align*}
{\it Accuracy}=&\frac{T P+T N}{T P+T N+F P+F N} \tag{8}
\\
{\it F}_{1}=&2\times \frac{Precision\times Recall}{Precision + Recall} \tag{9}
\\
{\it Recall}=&\frac{T P}{T P+F N} \tag{10}
\\
{\it Precision}=&\frac{T P}{T P+FP} \tag{11}
\end{align*}
\end{document}

Implementation details: We conduct experiments using the PyTorch framework and all the experiments are performed on two NVIDIA RTX 2080Ti GPUs.
1)
Segmentation Network: Each cross-domain combination model is trained 500 epochs with a batch size of 4, and all the modules are trained using Adam optimizer with initial learning rate of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
