sec.p:
We compare the performance of our proposed MS-AdaNet with unsupervised domain adaptation methods including CycleGAN [44], MUNIT [45], AdaptSegNet [35], SeUDA [43]. These methods utilize either image-to-image translation, feature adaptation or their mixtures. The first three methods have been validated in natural images. CycleGAN and MUNIT adapted image appearance, and AdaptSegNet employed output space adaptation. SeUDA dedicated to cross-domain lung segmentation using feature adaptation and image-to-image translation. We list the results of different methods in Table III, and the qualitative comparison are shown in Fig. 3. We noticed that the DSCs of CycleGAN and MUNIT for \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
